                           SourcePathResolver pathResolver,
                           PatternsMatcher entriesToExclude,
                           ZipCompressionLevel compressionLevel,
                           Zip.OnDuplicateEntryAction onDuplicateEntryAction)
        Create a UnarchiveAndZipStep to read from source files or zip files and write directly into a zip archive.

        Note that paths added to the archive are always relative to the working directory.

        For example, if you're in /dir and you add file.txt, you get an archive containing just the file. If you were in / and added dir/file.txt, you would get an archive containing the file within a directory. Sources and zip sources to include must be explicitly included.

        Parameters:
        filesystem - ProjectFilesystem project filesystem based in current working directory.
        basePath - working directory.
        pathToZipFile - output file for zip relative to the current working directory.
        sources - source files to add to the output zip.
        zipSources - zip files whose contents are added to the output zip.
        junkPaths - flatten the path to the source file.
        mergeSourceZips - if true then the contents of zip files listed in sources will be copied, otherwise, the entire file will be copied.
        pathResolver - resolves source paths to files.
        entriesToExclude - entries to exclude from the final zip. This only applies to names of sources or zipSources and not the files located within zipSources.
        compressionLevel - compression level of zip sources or zip sources.
